data.title: Zac Efron and Vanessa Hudgens on the Set of ‘High School Musical 2’
data.meta_description: Watch a bonus interview with the stars of the hit Disney musical.
data.text:
Right now, in Salt Lake City

shooting High School Musical 2.

I just finished Hairspray, up in Toronto, and then

right now, actually, I'm in the process of filming

High School Musical 2.

(upbeat rock music)

Going from project to project, the way I like to do it.

Both musicals so I'm kind of in the

swing of things right now.

I started home-schooling when I was in the 8th grade,

and my friends are going to prom but,

I never got invited.

In High School Musical 2, in a little portion,

in Troy's bedroom he has pictures of Troy and Gabriella

when we went to prom so we got to take pictures

of we went to prom in real prom outfits, you know.

So that was the closest I've gotten to prom though.

I went to lots of other people's proms,

as their date, but I didn't go to my own prom.

Our director, Kenny was telling us about how

he went to Hawaii and he got a massage on the beach

and he opens his eyes and he hears the roar of the ocean

and gosh, I just really wanna go.

No, my style is a little more...

I don't know. I think that the clothes that Gabriella wears

is a little sweeter than some of the stuff that I would wear

but still the same kinda thing.

A few of the dresses I picked out

'cause I really like them, but

I don't know. We're kinda similar in a way.

I love jewelry. I love this necklace.

It's really cute. A little lobster.

I love this too. I love skinny jeans.

You want my one tip, you want something

that I could never live without is

my eyelash curler (laughs).

I think I wanna do a movie. I'm not sure what yet.

And then after that I might record a second album.

I think I'm gonna be playing High School

for a little while longer.

But, I love it.

So much happens in High School

so you learn a lot about life.

I learned everything I know.
